    <article id="avotoast">
        <h2>Avocado Toast</h2>
            <img src="http://www.everythingerica.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Avocado-Toast-with-Chia-Seeds.jpg" 
             alt="Avocado toast on whole grain bread" title="Avocado Toast" width="300" />
        <p>Ingredients</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Whole Grain bread</li>
                <li>Ripe Hass Avocado</li>
                <li>Pink Salt</li>
            </ul>
            <details>
                <summary>Topping Suggestions</summary>
                    <ul>     
                        <li>Chia Seeds</li>
                        <li>Raw sliced almonds</li>
                        <li>Pumpkin Seeds</li>
                    </ul>
            </details>
        <p>Instructions</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Place bread in toaster</li>
            <li>While bread is toasting cut open the Avocado and mash the insides with a fork</li>
            <li>Spread smashed Avocado on toast</li>
            <li>Top with salt to taste, chia seeds, and almonds</li>
            <li>Get creative with your toppings!</li>
        
        </ol>
        <aside>
            <p class="comments">
            Avocado toast is a quick and nutritious breakfast option.
            </p>  
            <p class="comments">
            It can also be had as a treat or snack.
            </p>
       </aside>       
    </article>
    
    <article id="acai">
        <h2>Acai Bowl</h2>
        <img src="http://millennialmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Sambazon.jpg" 
             alt="Acai Bowl with toppings" title="Acai Bowl" width="300" />
        <p>Ingredients</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Sambazon Organic Acai Berry Packets</li>
            <li>8oz Almond Milk</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Honey <li>
            <li>Banana</li>
            <li>Chia Seeds</li>
            <li>Raw sliced almonds</li>
            <li>Coconut Chips</li>
            <li>Granola of choice</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Instructions</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Place Acai berry packet, half of the banana, honey and almond milk in blender</li>
            <li>Blend until thick and creamy</li>
            <li>Spread granola on bottom of medium sized bowl</li>
            <li>Pour smoothie over granola</li>
            <li>Top with remaining banana, chia seeds, coconut chips and almonds</li>
            <li>Get creative with your toppings!</li>
        
        </ol>
        <aside>
            <p class="comments">
            Acai berries are full of antioxidants and have been linked to weightloss!
            </p>  
            <p class="comments">
            If you're looking for a delicious treat with a nutrient punch, you've found it!
            </p>  
        </aside>
    </article>
    
    <article id="cauliflower">
        <h2>Roasted Cauliflower</h2>
        <img src="http://www.dinnerwithjulie.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Roasted-cauliflower-2.jpg" 
             alt="plated roasted cauliflower" title="Roasted Cauliflower" width="300" />
        <p>Ingredients</p>
        <ul>
            <li>1 Medium sized whole Cauliflower</li>
            <li><a href="http://www.thekitchn.com/how-to-roast-garlic-in-the-oven-5341" target="_blank">Roasted Garlic</a></li>
            <li>Pink Salt</li>
            <li>Black Pepper</li>
            <li>Olive Oil</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>Instructions</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Cut Cauliflower utilizing the florets only</li>
            <li>In a large bowl combine all other ingredients</li>
            <li>Toss cauliflower to evently coat</li>
            <li>Bake at 425&deg; for 30 minutes</li>
            <li>Feel free to cook longer if you prefer a darker roast</li>
        
        </ol>
        <aside>
            <p class="comments">
            Cauliflower is a low carbohydrate side that will satisfy even the hungriest of guests.
            </p>  
            <p class="comments">
            Fun Fact: 1 serving of cauliflower has the recommended amount of fiber for an enetire day!
            </p>  
        </aside>
    </article> 
    
